𝐈𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐯𝐢𝐞𝐰 𝐄𝐱𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞 𝐚𝐭 𝐀𝐭𝐥𝐚𝐬𝐬𝐢𝐚𝐧 – 𝐒𝐃𝐄 𝟐 𝐑𝐨𝐥𝐞

Recently interviewed at Atlassian. Sharing my experience to help anyone preparing for similar roles 👇

◼️ 𝟏𝐬𝐭 𝐑𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝 – 𝐊𝐚𝐫𝐚𝐭 𝐈𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐯𝐢𝐞𝐰 (𝟔𝟎 𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐬)
→ 10 mins: Brief project discussion
→ 20 mins: System design — 5 scenario-based questions focused on trade-offs and design decisions
→ 30 mins: DSA — 2 problems, had to solve at least 1 to proceed
✅ Needed to clear at least 1 DSA and 3 design scenarios to pass

◼️ 𝟐𝐧𝐝 𝐑𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝 – 𝐂𝐨𝐝𝐞 𝐃𝐞𝐬𝐢𝐠𝐧
→ Task: Design a Rate Limiter
→ Focus: Scalability, clean and maintainable code, modular design decisions

◼️ 𝟑𝐫𝐝 𝐑𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝 – 𝐌𝐚𝐜𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐂𝐨𝐝𝐢𝐧𝐠
→ Problem: Booking tennis courts based on availability and incoming requests
→ Key expectations: OOP design, edge case handling, writing production-level code

To clear interviews at PBCs like Atlassian, you need more than just practice—you need a SOLID roadmap that covers company-specific topics, DSA, scalable systems, etc.
